Fast-rising Nigerian Afropop musician, Okpowodu Ebiekemiete Johnson popularly known by the stage name Jayson has revealed why he ventured into music and how he hope to make positive impacts.According to the singer, who hails from Delta and Bayelsa states, he believes that his talents and creativity will pave way for him as time goes on.In his words, “I decided to go into music because I realized that’s what I’m good at the most, music is everything to me. If I wasn’t doing music I don’t know what I’ll be doing.“I know that nothing good comes easy, in a space where there’s an abundance in talents and creatives, I’m looking to create a path for myself that only few have chosen, wouldn’t want to reveal it all but I believe as time goes on things would begin to reveal themselves,” he said.Speaking about challenges in the industry, the graduate of Business Administration from Nigeria Delta University said it’s obvious funding is one of the major challenges.“I think the major challenge for me as an individual aside from the obvious which is looking for funding, I’ll like to say that it’s to find my sound.“I have stated earlier that the industry is filled with amazing talents, so trying to find myself, my sound, and my own uniqueness has been my greatest challenge, but I’m very positive that I believe I have what it takes to stand out in the industry because of my versatility, I can do anything. Just okay the beat, he added.